\emph{\textbf{Full-Solution Problems.} In questions 2-8, justify your
answers and \textbf{show all your work.} Simplification of answers is
not required unless explicitly stated.}

Let

\begin{align*}
\displaystyle
y=f(x)=6x^{1/5}+x^{6/5}
\end{align*}

Sketch the graph of $y=f(x)$ and indicate the inflection points on your
graph. Please also indicate the point(s) on your graph at which the
graph of $y=f(x)$ has a vertical tangent line.
